<b>Can be useful - </b>4/9/01 4:06:46 PM<br>~ <b>Belark Songstrider</b><blockquote>When is this song useful? A good question, but after some grouping I think I have found the answer.<br><br>If you are the primary haste provider for your party, and are going to be using weapons.. absolutely do NOT give up weapons in favor of singing this song. The 5% haste will not make up the damage you do with weapons.<br><br>However, if you are in INSTRUMENT ONLY mode AND your party is having HASTE SUPPLIED BY ENCHANTER OR SHAMAN, this song can be used to further boost the haste of the melee fighters. As an example, in Karnor's castle I frequently twist Catana of Soothing, Niv's Melody of Preservation, and this song during battle. This gives mana to the healers; strength, regen, and AC to all, and bonus haste for the melee. <br><br>So is this a completely useless song? No. It has a use. Just not a very common one.<br><br>As for paying 500-1000pp for it... don't. :) Go kill Guardian or Crystalline Shardwurms in the Great Divide for a few hours, and it should pop up. Not too rare.<br><br>-Belark Songstrider, 51st Minstrel of Drinal</blockquote></td></tr><tr bgcolor="#eeeeee"><td>
